@Node VERS "Version history"
0.1 (8th May 96): Pre-release
0.2 (14th May 96): Pre-release with minor improvements
0.3 (19th May 96): Introduction of buttons for page flipping and
		status information fields for loading functions;
		Optional preloading of thumbnails;
		Support of partial files
0.4 (21st May 96): Support for progressive JPeg pictures
0.5 (30th May 96): Change for better compatibility on Picassos WITHOUT CyberGraphX
0.9 (5th June 96): Directory/file parameters for WB start
		Configurability with WB-Tooltypes (e.g. ScreenMode, field size,
			subtitles, window dimensions etc.)
		Separate fonts for subtitles & gadgets can be configured (Tooltypes)
		Picture selection functions in the menu
		Status information for range of displayed thumbnails
		DOS requesters redirected to PhotoAlbum screen
		Less memory usage if multiple picture windows are opened
		Remove function to remove pictures from the thumbnail window
		Save and delete functions (full version only)
		Support of preview files in several formats
		Creation of preview files in several formats (full version only)
		Stop button to interrupt several actions
		Multiple selection support for double click picture opening
1.0/a (11th June 96): Database concept for maintainance of preview files across
			multiple volumes (full version only)
		Menu function to add additional pictures/directiries etc.
		Configurable cache memory limit for thumbnails
		Thumbnail cache memory release function
		Information windows with detailled informations about selected pictures
		Status information window with information about all scanned files
		Gadget for editable file comment (optional) (full version only)
		Function to create preview files for new pictures only (full version)
		New saving function: IFF-RGBN (compressed 12Bit format); usable for
			full pictures and preview files (full version only)
		Direct transfer functions to ImageFX and XiPaint (full version only)
		Bug fixes in menu flag handling
1.0a2 (19th June 96): Corrected misspelling in Icon-Tooltype "WindowWidth" which
			let PhotoAlbum ignore this tooltype if used unchanged
1.1 (23rd June 96): Optional fine (but slower) scaling for JPeg pictures
			during loading (menue and Tooltype)
		Buf fixes of minor status displaying bugs
		Disabling of menues/gadgets during preview file creation
1.2 (28th June 96): Easier screenmode configuration with the tooltypes
			"Width", "Height" and "Depth" (even if you have CGfx problems)
		Tooltype "ShowDataBase" for automatic viewing of a database
		Menu function to delete selected preview files
1.2a (28th July 96): Fixed bugs in error handling of preview file creation
			(e.g. for "volume full" or similair problems)
1.3 (13th Aug. 96): Extended loading functions for new variants of IFF-DEEP
			(e.g. as created by TVPaint 3)
2.0 (27th Aug. 96): Copy function to copy groups of selected pictures to a
			new directory
		Functions to invoke ARexx commands for loading into ImageFX&Photogenics
		Function to invoke a user definable ARexx command; can also
			be configured to start external viewers! Preconfigured
			to start CyberShow
2.1 (17th Sep. 96): Inclusion of german program version
2.2 (11th Oct. 96): Optional catalog concept for compact storage of large
			thumbnail collections in a single file
		Invoke ARexx commands for loading into ADPro, PPaint and XiPaint
		Integrated ARexx command functions to directly invoke CyberShow
			and CyberTVPlayer for selected files
		Improved error handling and status information for ARexx functions
		Thumbnail field size 80x60 now selectable by menu
		Improvement of error handling (esp. for out of memory situations)
			during thumbnail loading or preview file creation
		Correction of some minor bugs
2.3 (23rd Oct. 96): Extended loading functions for IFF-ILBM 15Bit format
2.4 (6th Nov. 96): Faster directory scanning esp. for CD-ROMs and catalog files
		Bug fixes in PCX planar file loading
		Script controlled slideshow presentation with CyberShow Pro (V8.x);
		  presentation options configurable by tooltype.
2.4a (23rd Nov. 96): Bug fix for handling of corrupt IFF-ILBM files
2.5 (10th Dec. 96): For PhotoAlbum/CyberShow package users:
			PhotoAlbum screen is now a public screen and thus can
			 be used shared with CyberShow or CyberTVPlayer for
			 displaying.
			New menu functions to call thoose programs in windows
			 on the PhotoAlbum screen, including autoscale option.
			Built-in CyberShow calls extended by PF option.
3.0 (4th Mar. 97): Support for configuration file saving and automatic
			configuration loading on program start
3.1 (29th Mar. 97): Shell parameter support for comfortable start of PhotoAlbum
			from shells, other programs or scripts
		    AutoCache function (menu,tooltype,parameter) for automatic
			adaption of thumbnail cache limit to free memory size
3.2 (7th Apr. 97): Page flipping can now be done with cursor keys left/right
		   Closing picture windows now possible with Esc key
3.2a (9th May 97): Bug fix of menu flag displaying for progressive-JPeg-saving
3.3 (28th June 97): Selectable warning before overwriting of picture files
			(during conversion or copying of pictures)
		    Bug fix of menu flag displaying for several option flags
3.3a/b (Nov.97/Jan.98): Documentational updates: New EMail address, sidegrade offers
3.4 (17th Jan. 98): Selectable warning before quitting of program
3.5 (14th Feb. 98): ARexx controlled transfer functions to ArtEffect
			(for ArtEffect 2.5 and up) as picture and as brush
3.5a (7th Mar. 98): Bug-Fix for extension of existing catalog files by pictures
		    Small Bug-Fixes for memory handling of DType/EPS/YUV/HHsYUVSq
4.0 (21st Mar. 98):24Bit Datatype support (for the 24Bit datatype of the
			Picasso 96 system and maybe also for the 24Bit DT of
			the CyberGraphX system, unless that DT is expired).
			Allows loading of specific file formats with matching
			Datatypes in 24Bit quality (useful e.g. for PNG) and
			with a sometimes faster chunky interface. The 24Bit
			interface usage can be switched by menu settings.
			If no suitable 24Bit picture.datatype is found the old
			interface will be used automatically.
		  Datatype control: By settings menu or tooltype you can also
			switch off all datatype usage.
			Useful if you have some instable Datatypes installed on
			your system and you want to scan large directories without
			problems only for internally supported pictures.
		  JPegViaDT: This option will try to load JPeg full pictures with
			Datatypes before using internal JPeg loading.
			Useful if you have e.g. a fas PowerPC board and JPeg
			datatype written for it. Also useable to get 256 colored
			dithered output (for users of 256 color screens) if
			you configure your JPeg datatype that way (in this case
			you may have to also switsch 24Bit DT off).
		  Memory release for datatypes.library fixed.
4.1 (14th Apr. 98): Accelerated catalog file loading (esp. much higher speed for
			loading of large catalog files created sorted by pathname and
			on slow exchangable disk medias; speed up upto factor 12!)
4.1a (23rd May 98): Correction of memory usage/size display (for more than 32MByte)
5.0 (10th Aug. 98): New button for last page displaying and enhanced backward page
			flipping functionality (e.g. after changed frame sizes)
		    Sorting functions (in menu) for sorting according to path, name,
			comment, type, file size and dimensions (see menu functions)
6.0 (19th Okt. 98): HTML page creation from picture collections with thumbnail pictures
			(JPeg or IFF format), link to full pictures and selectable
			picture subtitles (name, comment etc.) as in PhotoAlbum.
			Use of the HTML pages in web browsers like AWeb or also on
			other computeer systems with Netscape or Explorer;
			also useful to print PhotoAlbum picture collections with
			web browsers!
6.1 (18th Dec. 98): Option for fixing of picture window size during outzooming
			functions (downscaled viewing) during viewing (Menu setting);
			this menu setting is also saveable in configuration file.
6.1a (3rd Jan. 99): Registration prices converted to Euro; price reductions for
			sidegrades and some foreign currencies.
6.2 (28th Feb. 99): File changing date can be selected as subtitle now
		    File changing date&time can now be used for sorting order
		    Scrolling of full size picture windows is now possible by
			"dragging" the picture while the left mouse button is pressed
		    MinimumFileSize: Tooltype and shell parameter (MinFS) to set
			a limit for a minimum file size; all files smaller than this
			will be ignored. Useful e.g. to filter out small read-me
			files or small images from browser caches. Range 0-65535 bytes.
6.3 (12th Apr. 99): Enhancement of diagonal scrolling functions (esp. for "dragging"
			of a picture in a window with the mouse)
6.3a (3rd May 99): Bug-fixes for scrolling functions during magnified viewing
6.3b (10th May 99): Bug-fix for mouse-drag scrolling functions (reduced&normal viewing)
6.3c (26th Aug.99): Work around in HTML page creation: Some file systems
			(e.g. for hard disks under the Amiga simulator UAE)
			do not support certain DOS packets. The HTML page
			creation will now use another method in this case.
			To also get the relativ path name creation to work
			with this you have to enter the path of the html
			file in exactly the form (volume name and path in
			correct capitalization) as the path of the pictures.
6.4 (4th Nov. 99): Configurable double clicking action: select internal
			window viewing, CyberShow presentation or external
			ARexx command invocation.
		   Further bug-fix for scrolling/zooming during magnification
6.5 (24rd Dec. 99): Fast direct transfer to fxPaint (with Stargate plugin)
		    Bug-fix for magnified scrolling/resizing functions
6.5a (15th Apr. 2000): Documentational update: Order and delivery by E-Mail possible.

6.6 (27th Dec.2001): Manual picture rotation function (+/-90 degree and 180 degree)
		      is now available in the full size picture menues.
		  Automatic picture rotation for Sony DSC Cybershot pictures
		  (rotation detection for photos from other cameras might be
		   included in future, if I get such information. Please contact me.).
		  Public screen name handling extended to support use of PhotoAlbum
		   on several screens (new names will be PhotoAlbum2 upto PhotoAlbum9).
		  Delete warning requester extended by a gadget to switch off further
		   appearance of that requester (useful if you have to delete many files).
		  Extended full picture window functions by delete (deletes the picture
		   file and closes all related windows) and remove (just removes the
		   picture from the current PhotoAlbum session and closes related
		   windows, but without deleting the file). These functions were
		   formerly only available from the preview window.
		  New homepage and email address.
		  New registration prices (33% cheaper email registrations).

Please register now, so that the development can go on!
@EndNode
